  <h1>Charli-Jo Tyrer</h1>

  <p class="site-intro">The public home of Charli-Jo Tyrer.</p>
  <p>Charli-Jo Tyrer is a blind writer, conceptual artist and accessibility thinker working with generative AI, design fiction and agent-first digital systems.</p>
  <p>My work explores what happens when accessibility, artificial intelligence and design fiction begin shaping the same future.</p>

  <div class="destinations">
    <section class="destination destination-art" aria-labelledby="blind-ant-heading">
      <h2 id="blind-ant-heading">Blind Ant</h2>
      <p>Blind Ant is the conceptual art practice of Charli-Jo Tyrer, using generative AI as an artistic medium.</p>
      <p>The work explores identity, disability, technology, power, care and the strange systems people build around themselves.</p>
      <p><a class="destination-link" href="/blind-ant/">Go to Blind Ant</a></p>
    </section>

    <section class="destination destination-access" aria-labelledby="carrados-heading">
      <h2 id="carrados-heading">Carrados</h2>
      <p>Carrados is Charli-Jo Tyrer's accessibility and agent-first design work. It explores how AI systems, websites and digital services can reduce informational suffering rather than reproduce it.</p>
      <p>Carrados is also home to Zero Information Casualty (ZIC), a design standard for preserving information across people, interfaces and AI agents.</p>
      <p><a class="destination-link" href="/carrados/">Go to Carrados</a></p>
    </section>
  </div>
